<p>I know you can add a parent selector like this:</p>  <pre><code>.main-selector {    .parent-selector &amp; {     } } </code></pre>  <p>I'm trying to figure out if there is a way to go back to the .main-selector so I can add a hover state style to a child element. So, something like this:</p>  <pre><code>.main-selector {    .child-selector {       *styles*       .main-selector:hover &amp; {          *hover styles*       }    } } </code></pre>